  "prompt": "How do I export onion from india to london?",
  "response": "To export onions from India to London, you'll need to follow these key steps:\n\n1. Legal and Regulatory Requirements:\n- Obtain an Export License\n- Get APEDA (Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development Authority) registration\n- Comply with UK import regulations\n- Secure phytosanitary certificates\n- Meet quality and safety standards\n\n2. Documentation Needed:\n- Commercial Invoice\n- Packing List\n- Certificate of Origin\n- Bill of Lading/Airway Bill\n- Phytosanitary Certificate\n- Import License from UK\n\n3. Export Preparation:\n- Select high-quality onions\n- Proper cleaning and grading\n- Appropriate packaging\n- Temperature-controlled storage\n- Proper handling to maintain quality\n\n4. Shipping Methods:\n- Sea freight (container shipping)\n- Air freight\n- Choose based on cost and urgency\n\n5. Customs Clearance:\n- Prepare all necessary documentation\n- Pay required duties and taxes\n- Clear UK customs regulations\n\n6. Additional Considerations:\n- Check current trade agreements\n- Understand import quotas\n- Consider shipping costs\n- Comply with UK food safety standards\n\nConsulting with an export/import specialist or freight forwarder is recommended for specific guidance.",
